22:17.333 --> 22:19.250
♪ Whoo! ♪

22:19.250 --> 22:21.625
Namaste, namaste, namaste!

22:21.625 --> 22:22.834
Where the hell have you been?

22:22.834 --> 22:26.417
In mourning and meditation
after the death of your mother.

22:26.417 --> 22:28.000
Acceptance, resurrection,

22:28.000 --> 22:30.834
enlightenment.

22:30.834 --> 22:32.500
And...

22:32.500 --> 22:37.125
we have to deny the existence
of a permanent entity

22:37.125 --> 22:38.875
that remains constant
behind the changing

22:38.875 --> 22:42.375
corporal or incorporal
components of a living being.

22:42.375 --> 22:45.166
All things are in
a constant state of flux.

22:45.166 --> 22:46.583
All is changing,

22:46.583 --> 22:48.500
and no permanent state
exists by itself.

22:48.500 --> 22:51.333
Your mother--
Holy Buddha rest her soul--

22:51.333 --> 22:53.750
stole my chakra
when I was 20 years old,

22:53.750 --> 22:55.583
and she kept it until her death,

22:55.583 --> 22:57.417
and now she's gone.

22:57.417 --> 22:59.500
And I'm free.

23:01.166 --> 23:03.375
Can I use the shower?

23:03.375 --> 23:06.834
Or-or--but--
unless you were planning

23:06.834 --> 23:08.625
to take a shower soon.

23:08.625 --> 23:10.417
No. Uh, I'm good.

23:10.417 --> 23:12.583
Want me to sell
any of that meth?

23:12.583 --> 23:16.333
Soon as I sell Ian's,
I could find a buyer for yours.

23:16.333 --> 23:18.583
No need. I smoked it.

23:18.583 --> 23:20.041
An entire pound?

23:20.041 --> 23:21.083
What? [laughs]

23:21.083 --> 23:23.500
No, like, half.

23:23.500 --> 23:26.875
I gave the rest away
to the needy.

23:26.875 --> 23:28.667
Damn.

23:28.667 --> 23:30.542
[groans]

23:32.208 --> 23:33.625
Nasty side effects, though.

23:35.709 --> 23:37.041
[horn honks]

23:37.041 --> 23:38.500
My Bubble Master.

23:44.417 --> 23:46.417
It's beautiful.

23:46.417 --> 23:48.166
You used your mother's
inheritance to buy that?

23:48.166 --> 23:49.375
Yeah.

23:49.375 --> 23:50.542
She'd love it, son.

23:53.542 --> 23:56.250
Eight blocks north,
up by the park.

23:56.250 --> 23:58.083
One-bedrooms are going
for a thousand.

23:58.083 --> 23:58.750
Eight blocks north
up by the park

23:58.750 --> 24:00.542
has an El stop, a Starbucks,

24:00.542 --> 24:02.458
and they're building
a Whole Foods.

24:03.834 --> 24:05.250
Hey, Sierra.

24:05.250 --> 24:06.417
Can you take
the girls out back

24:06.417 --> 24:07.709
and get some
chili cheese nachos,

24:07.709 --> 24:09.250
extra cheese,

24:09.250 --> 24:10.583
and some Mountain Dew,
but no refills?

24:10.583 --> 24:12.166
So I just walked
by the Alibi...

24:12.166 --> 24:13.750
Mm-hmm.

24:13.750 --> 24:14.542
And it's not called
the Alibi anymore.

24:14.542 --> 24:17.625
- What?
- Putin's Paradise.

24:17.625 --> 24:19.291
Bunch of Russian flags
out front,

24:19.291 --> 24:21.542
and it was crowded--
I peeked.

24:21.542 --> 24:23.083
That bitch is gettin' rich

24:23.083 --> 24:24.500
and we can barely put food
on the table?

24:24.500 --> 24:26.250
We have to go back
to the lawyer.

24:26.250 --> 24:27.792
Oh, V, the lawyer said

24:27.792 --> 24:29.166
there's nothing
they can do for us.

24:29.166 --> 24:30.250
Then we have to find
new lawyers.

24:30.250 --> 24:31.542
Svetlana's Russian.

24:31.542 --> 24:33.291
Russians always win.

24:33.291 --> 24:35.458
That's not true.
Miracle on Ice?

24:35.458 --> 24:37.000
Well, they usually win,

24:37.000 --> 24:39.166
what with the winners
in the KGB

24:39.166 --> 24:41.500
and them pumping their athletes
full of so much steroids

24:41.500 --> 24:44.625
that their women grow beards
and their testicles drop.

24:46.375 --> 24:48.250
You think I could ask for 900?

24:48.250 --> 24:50.291
